# api-endpoints

## Meeting Routes
Implements domain-specific meeting management with signal extraction:

1. Meeting Creation & Analysis
- POST /meetings/create
  - Extracts business signals from meeting content
  - Categorizes into: decisions, actions, blockers, risks, ideas
  - Generates meeting summary with signal highlighting

2. Meeting Signal Management 
- POST /meetings/{id}/signals
  - Processes new signals identified during meetings
  - Links signals to relevant tickets and sprints
  - Maintains signal status workflow (approved, rejected, archived)

3. Meeting Context Integration
- GET /meetings/{id}/context
  - Retrieves related documents and previous meetings
  - Builds knowledge graph connections
  - Maps signals to DIKW hierarchy levels

## Document Routes
Handles document processing with business context:

1. Document Processing
- POST /documents/upload
  - Extracts meeting-style signals from documents
  - Maps document sections to knowledge categories
  - Links documents to related meetings

2. Document Signals
- GET /documents/{id}/signals
  - Retrieves extracted business signals
  - Provides signal status and relationships
  - Shows document-to-meeting signal mappings

